# QPU truth-table protection

- Never edit bundled or site-provided `.qpuio` files for `SingleBitFullAdder`, `TwoBitFullAdder`, `FourBitFullAdder`, or `PhaseDemo` in pull requests.
- Canonical tables live in `src/data/processes/*.qpuio` and are enforced at runtime via `src/data/protectedQpuio.ts`.
- To change expectations for experiments, register a new uploaded/corrected catalog process instead of mutating bundled metadata.
- Follow `AGENTS.md` for Correction Lab LLM behavior and child-process compatibility requirements.
- Follow `CLAUDE.md` for Claude-specific workflow and repository conventions.
